From bb06b4808be7729382866a233b6a996849a4707a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Date: Sat, 5 Mar 2022 23:12:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] wireless: Use netif_rx().

References: bnc#1189998 (PREEMPT_RT prerequisite backports)
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
Git-commit: f9834dbdd322f144f7b51f2fe8017fc6b870b3ec

Since commit
   baebdf48c3600 ("net: dev: Makes sure netif_rx() can be invoked in any context.")

the function netif_rx() can be used in preemptible/thread context as
well as in interrupt context.

Use netif_rx().

Cc: Johannes Berg <johannes@sipsolutions.net>
Cc: linux-wireless@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Mel Gorman <mgorman@suse.de>
---
 net/wireless/util.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/util.c b/net/wireless/util.c
index 4ddc269164f8..52ed304bcec6 100644
--- a/net/wireless/util.c
+++ b/net/wireless/util.c
@@ -2149,7 +2149,7 @@ void cfg80211_send_layer2_update(struct net_device *dev, const u8 *addr)
 	skb->dev = dev;
 	skb->protocol = eth_type_trans(skb, dev);
 	memset(skb->cb, 0, sizeof(skb->cb));
-	netif_rx_ni(skb);
+	netif_rx(skb);
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(cfg80211_send_layer2_update);
 
